// Note: this obligation is genuinely unprovable in Verus.
    // The hypothesis provides r1@ == self_.my_end_point() and r2@ == self_.my_end_point(),
    // which yields r1.id@ == r2.id@ (Seq<u8> equality).
    // But the conclusion requires r1.id == r2.id (Vec<u8> equality), and in Verus,
    // == on Vec is opaque/strictly stronger than view equality.
    assert((r1@ == self_.my_end_point() && r2@ == self_.my_end_point()) ==> r1.id@ == r2.id@);
